<TEXT>
like millions of other soviets touched by the 
terror of josef stalin dmitri a volkogonov still remembers the 
day his father disappeared 
more than 50 years later that personal tragedy is foremost in 
volkogonovs mind as he finishes the first comprehensive soviet 
biography of stalin the man he blames for the death of his father 
and those of millions of others 
volkogonov a military historian said he has spent 10 years 
culling soviet archives and talking to people who knew stalin for a 
twovolume biography triumph and tragedy scheduled to appear 
next year 
there is no thorough soviet biography of stalin who killed 
millions of people through his forced collectivizaton of 
agriculture that began in 1929 and the political purges that 
followed in the next decade 
volkogonov told reporters wednesday his book will give an 
unofficial estimate of the number killed but he declined to reveal 
what it was 
as director of the defense ministrys institute of military 
history and earlier as deputy chief of the defense ministrys 
political directorate volkogonov a colonelgeneral has had 
unusual access to longsuppressed official information about stalin 
nobody in this country has as many documents on this man as i 
do said volkogonov wearing an army uniform emblazoned with rows 
of multicolored military decorations 
the documents as well as interviews with people who knew him 
show stalin to be one of the most terrible figures in mankind 
said volkogonov 
my father was a direct victim of stalins purges the 
historian said he was an agronomist and somebody didnt like 
him once he was summoned to a certain meeting and he never 
returned he was 36 years old 
that was 1937 when volkogonov was 8 years old 
volkogonov said the disappearance of his father haunted him for 
years 
when i was already an old man people would deal with me with 
suspicion because i was the son of an enemy of the people he 
recalled referring to the label stalin used to brand those he 
considered his opponents 
volkogonov is among those tapped to correct the record as the 
countrys reformminded leader mikhail s gorbachev tries to 
reexamine the whitewashing of stalins crimes in history books and 
the official press 
the issue is at the forefront this week as the party holds its 
first nationwide conference since the last one stalin called in 
1941 volkogonov is a delegate to the conference which is 
reviewing proposals to correct deformations stalin caused in 
the party and society 
nikita s khrushchev was the first soviet leader to shake the 
world with the enormity of stalins crimes in 1956 his charges 
against stalin were made in secret to a party congress and 
disclosed only unofficially 
more than 31 years later at a public forum nov 2 marking the 
70th anniversary of the bolshevik revolution gorbachev accused 
stalin of enormous and unforgiveable crimes and dismissed any 
notion that the former dictator didnt know about those who died 
because of his excesses 
gorbachevs criticism sparked a wave of soviet press reports 
including ones by volkogonov about stalins crimes writing in 
december in the literary weekly literaturnaya gazeta volkogonov 
said stalins repressions were a result of the tragic triumph of 
evil force and who knows was there together with cruelty a 
neverrecognized spiritual illness of stalin 
last week the party newspaper pravda published excerpts from 
volkogonovs biography in which the author denounced the dictator 
for signing a friendship treaty with nazi germany and crippling his 
own army by purging its officer corps before world war ii 
some conservatives have suggested stalin was not aware of the 
extent of repression under him but at a news conference wednesday 
volkogonov said he had found evidence to the contrary 
there were personal orders about terrorism and the elimination 
of people he said but there was also inertia which he caused 
he couldnt predict what the volume of this inertia would be 
in several cases volkogonov said he found papers accusing 
people of crimes and stalins writing in the margins that he agreed 
with the charges 
asked if he agreed with western historians that stalin was 
behind the assassinations of political rivals sergei kirov in 1934 
and leon trotsky in mexico in 1937 volkogonov said he found no 
evidence stalin directly ordered the killings but that he had made 
it clear his aides were to remove all potential opposition 
</TEXT>
