a jury wednesday convicted of woman of 
gouging out a teenagers eye with her finger during an exorcism a 
year ago 
the jury took 20 minutes to find 26yearold andrea cowan guilty 
of cruelty to a juvenile darnell washington now 17 
the former state clerical worker who told police she conducted 
at least six exorcisms at her baptist church could receive up to 10 
years in prison at sentencing sept 9 
according to testimony a houseful of people prayed for 
washington as he writhed on the floor spitting foaming at the 
mouth and speaking in strange voices 
cowan her husband and her brotherinlaw a baptist pastor 
were summoned to help rid the boy of the supposed demons after he 
uttered what he said were vile things against god 
washington who now has a glass eye testified that he 
remembered everyone praying over him then being alone in the 
living room with cowan as she beat on the back of his head bit his 
ear and plucked my eye 
defense attorney john calmes had argued that washington was in a 
psychotic state and plucked his own eye out 
ms cowan prayed on him she laid hands on him and thats all 
she did he said 
