<TEXT>
more than 1500 peasants protesting the dumping 
of polluted water clashed near beijing with armed police who beat 
them with clubs and electric batons witnesses said 
they said more than 150 people were arrested 
the farmers from the village of guce 37 miles southwest of 
beijing were trying to stop a petrochemical plant from releasing 
contaminated water that would poison their wells when they clashed 
with thousands of armed police on june 21 villagers said 
villagers told western reporters earlier in the week that three 
people died but were unable today to confirm the deaths 
about 150 people including some high school students were 
arrested during the protest most were released later the same day 
or the following day but at least 10 remain in custody their 
whereabouts unknown 
we dont even know if they are dead or alive one woman said 
between 60 and 70 people were seriously injured in the melee 
with police wielding electric batons and nightsticks witnesses 
said 
estimates of the number of armed police ranged from 2000 to 
6000 villagers said police surrounded the village and occupied 
the village square for two days 
the district communist party secretarys office today refused to 
answer any questions relating to the incident saying that all 
inquiries had to be handled by the beijing foreign affairs office 
the foreign affairs office said it had just heard about the 
incident and was unable to give any details or answer questions 
the incident has not been reported by the chinese staterun news 
media 
villagers said they were told by authorities that water from a 
reservoir 12 miles north of guce used to store chemical waste 
from the stateowned yanshan petrochemical co would have to be 
released to avoid flooding during the wet season 
we asked them not to release the water because it would harm 
everyone in the village one woman said 
witnesses said the trouble started at about 1 am on june 21 
when villagers learned that the water was to be released that day 
three days earlier than they had been told 
through the night around 1500 guce residents gathered at the 
reservoir to protest armed police arrived at about 3 am and 
began indiscriminately beating the peasants eyewitnesses said 
villagers said beijing vice mayor zhang jianming was at the 
scene 
one villager said protesters standing in or near the creek into 
which the reservoirs water was to be released were shocked by 
police who stuck their electric batons in the water 
many of those seriously hurt sustained head injuries one high 
school student was reported to have been hit nearly 200 times with 
an electric baton 
just about everyone who was there was injured in some way 
one old man said 
water was released from the reservoir at about 440 am and by 
5 am the protestors disbanded beaten into submission by the 
armed police one villager said 
today the main village road was blocked to traffic as workers 
began digging trenches to install water pipes villagers said their 
well water has been contaminated by the chemical waste 
temporary pipes were installed to bring clean water to some 
outdoor spigots but farmers said there was not enough to water 
their crops which also have been contaminated 
we cant plant anything now everythings dried up and 
theres no water for the fields one farmer said 
those who live in the village of 4700 complained that the 
contaminated water brought on a variety of ailments including 
headaches and nosebleeds 
one young man pointed to itchy red spots all over his shoulders 
and chest which he claimed were caused by the water 
a woman carrying a baby said we all were affected the 
children were coughing all night long 
