<TEXT>
in a landmark decision a magistrate court 
today sentenced four israeli leftwing activists to sixmonth 
prison terms for violating a law that bars contacts with the plo 
they were the first israelis to be jailed on the basis of the 
1986 law barring unauthorized contacts with members of 
terrorist groups israel views the plo as a terrorist group 
a judge in this city near tel aviv also gave each of the four a 
oneyear suspended sentence and ruled that each should pay 2500 
in fines and court expenses the law carries a sentence of up to 
three years imprisonment 
they seemed thunderstruck when they heard the ruling one 
witness told the associated press 
the leftists were convicted on june 2 for violating the law by 
meeting with a 15member palestine liberation organization group in 
costinesti romania in november 1986 
israel army radio quoted judge avraham baiser as acknowledging 
in his ruling that the law was disputed in israel 
however the law should be respected even if it is not 
accepted by the public baiser wrote the court is not to 
decide whether a law is bad or good the accused have committed an 
offense in front of the eyes of the whole world and now they should 
be punished 
