the vatican today announced the 
excommunication of archbishop marcel lefebvre and four bishops he 
consecrated 
a statement read by vatican spokesman joaquin navarro cited 
church law for the excommunications noting the prohibition on 
consecrating bishops without papal approval 
in such cases the excommunication is automatic requiring no 
formal act by the vatican only the pope can lift the sanction 
navarro said 
the statement made shortly after lefebvre carried out the 
consecrations in econe switzerland said it was a schismatic act 
carried out expressly against the wishes of the pope 
a schism is a formal rupture with the holy see 
excommunication puts a roman catholic outside the church and 
unable to receive its sacraments such as communion and extreme 
unction or last rites 
earlier this week lefebvres traditionalist movement challenged 
the excommunications claiming that church law permits such 
ordinations in an emergency 
the vatican said the only necessity in the case was raised 
by lefebvre to conserve an attitude of division in the catholic 
church despite the offers of communion and concessions made by the 
holy father john paul ii 
navarro said a statement would be issued in coming days on the 
position of lefebvres lay followers 
the communique identified those excommunicated as lefebvre and 
the four bishops bernard fellay bernard tissier de mallerais 
richard williamson and alfonso de galarreta 
brazilian prelate antonio de castro mayer bishop of campos 
assisted at the rites in econe navarro said the vatican was 
