1982 as the longest peacetime expansion in history and took a 
swipe at economists for being pessimistic 
economists arent any help he said noting that leading 
economists have been projecting a recession since 1984 and two 
years ago 60 percent of the members of the national association of 
business economics predicted a downturn in 1988 
wrong wrong wrong bush said no wonder its called the 
dismal science 
im feeling like harry truman bush added forty years 
ago he was fighting against the odds and when he went out to 
speak the crowds would yell give em hell and hed shout back 
i dont have to give em hell i just tell the truth and they 
think its hell bush said 
bush also reiterated his call for tougher sentences for drug 
abusers in a speech to the national organization of black law 
enforcement officers 
only 14 percent of the drug felons convicted in new york city 
last year were sentenced to as much as a year with no probation 
he said in prepared remarks 
he said that states should make more use of habitual 
offender laws that make repeated conviction on felony charges a 
separate crime and proposed providing federal jail space for 
them when needed 
bush was scheduled to leave thursday night for his vacation 
resort in kennebunkport maine where he will spend most of the 
holiday weekend on the fourth of july bush planned to visit four 
cities including detroit and st louis to participate in 
independence day events 
