john demjanjuk appealed his conviction and 
death sentence for nazi war crimes thursday contending a lynch 
atmosphere pervaded the court that found him guilty of mutilating 
and killing death camp inmates 
the retired ohio autoworkers lawyers asked the supreme court to 
reverse his conviction due to lack of proof and much more than 
substantial doubt that he was the brutal ukrainian guard called 
ivan the terrible by inmates of the treblinka concentration 
camp 
demjanjuk who is 68 and was born in the ukraine was sentenced 
april 25 a week after being found guilty of operating the gas 
chambers that killed 850000 jews in 194243 at the camp in 
nazioccupied poland he claims to be a victim of mistaken identity 
speaking in an interview at the supreme court defense lawyer 
yoram sheftel said the 101page appeal challenged every finding 
of the court as far as facts and legal aspects and accused the 
three district court judges of acting in a biased and uncivilized 
way 
it accused the judges of extreme and unprecedented involvement 
in questioning witnesses that in effect made them prosecutors 
state television which broadcast the trial daily and other 
israeli media conducted an organized massive campaign 
against the defendant the appeal said and all this 
contributed to a lynch atmosphere which completely undermined 
any possibility of a fair trial 
defense lawyers also contended in the appeal that two groups of 
photos used by camp survivors to identify the defendant were 
unpermissibly suggestive 
they said no evidence was produced to challenge demjanjuks 
story that he was in a german prisonerofwar camp during the time 
in question he was taken prisoner while serving in the soviet army 
sheftel said he visited demjanjuk last week at his maximum 
security cell in ayalon prison near tel aviv and he was fine he 
is optomistic and looking forward to the appeal 
supreme court spokesman shmaryahu cohen said a fivejudge panel 
headed by chief justice meir shamgar will hear the appeal from dec 
57 and dec 1214 
the prosecution is scheduled to reply sometime between dec 19 
and dec 29 chief prosecutor yonah blattmans office declined to 
comment on the appeal saying prosecutors had not yet received a 
copy 
demjanjuk moved to the united states after world war ii and 
settled in the cleveland suburb of seven hills he was stripped of 
us citizenship asnd extradited after a court ruled he had lied on 
his application to become an american citizen 
if demjanjuk is hanged he will be the first person executed in 
israel since nazi war criminal adolf eichmann was put to death in 
1962 after a trial in jerusalem 
israeli agents kidnapped eichmann the architect of adolf 
hitlers mass extermination of jews in argentina in 1960 
