<TEXT>
the remains of composer bela bartok 
arrived in europe from new york on thursday for burial in his 
native hungary next week 
a brownpainted wooden box with brass corners and orangered wax 
seals along the edges of the lid held the remains of the master of 
modern musical composition who died in 1945 and was buried in new 
yorks ferncliff cemetery 
the box stood in an otherwise empty storeroom on a lower deck of 
the liner queen elizabeth 2 which left new york on saturday and 
arrived at its home port of southampton in bright sunshine 
earlier reports said bartok who died of leukemia in new york in 
1945 was buried in new yorks ferncliff cemetery in a steel coffin 
because all who knew him were certain he would one day be 
reinterred in his native land 
a steel coffin would have been easier to move but someone 
cheated us in 1945 said the composers younger son peter 64 a 
sound recording engineer from homosassa fla north of tampa 
steel was ordered but the undertakers buried him in wood when 
we dug up our father the wood had disintegrated and there wasnt 
enough left to cover my thumbnail he said 
peter and his brother bela 78 an engineer who lives in 
budapest and is president of hungarys unitarian church crossed 
the ocean with their fathers remains 
the brothers will attend the funeral in farkasret cemetery 
budapest july 7 their mother is buried there as is hungarys 
other famous modern composer zoltan kodaly who died in 1967 
when reporters saw the box in 5 deck aft recess it was 
undecorated although in new york it had been covered with ribbons 
in the hungarian red white and green colors 
the sons were met on the quayside by matyas domokos hungarys 
ambassador to britain and pat bear mayor of southampton who wore 
her gold chain of office over a blue dress 
we felt we had to be here to show respect to bela bartok 
said mrs bear 
i think it is good that we are doing this i know hungary 
wants it said the composers elder son 
the two sons were driven to city hall for tea and then taken on 
a tour of southampton 
a memorial concert was scheduled at the turner sims concert 
hall part of southampton university 
bartoks body was in a coffin enclosed in a shipping crate 
covered with ribbons in the hungarian colors red white and green 
we know that bela bartok did not want to rest in eternal 
exile but the family for a long time were reluctant to disturb his 
grave said gabor horvath press attache at the hungarian embassy 
it has been a longstanding wish of our government and nation 
to rebury bela bartok in budapest as one of hungarys greatest sons 
and our greatest composer of the 20th century horvath said 
the diplomat said the coffin would remain on the liner overnight 
for fridays sailing to cherbourg in france the coffin will then 
travel through france west germany and austria to hungary where 
bartok was born at nagyszentmiklos on march 25 1881 his 
birthplace is now in romania and renamed sinnicolau mare 
</TEXT>
