<TEXT>
archbishop marcel lefebvre defied the 
pope and consecrated four bishops thursday causing the first roman 
catholic schism in a century and his own expulsion from the church 
that was his life for 60 years 
the 82yearold rebel prelate who has spent a generation 
fighting the satanic influence of modernism rejected a 
lastminute appeal from pope john paul ii he looked pale and tired 
under his white goldembroidered miter as he conducted the rite 
that split the faith for the first time since 1870 
lefebvre performed the historic act in a huge sweltering tent 
in a meadow below the seminary he founded in this hillside hamlet 
18 years ago and named the st pius x fraternity for the pope who 
condemned modernism in a 1907 encyclical 
his chosen mass as usual was the 16th century tridentine rite 
in latin which was replaced by the vernacular under the 196265 
second vatican council reforms he detests 
a vatican statement issued less than two hours later condemned 
the consecrations as an act of schism a formal break with the holy 
see that had not occurred since the socalled old catholics 
rebelled when the doctrine of papal infallibility was proclaimed 
it announced the excommunication of lefebvre and the four new 
bishops british french spanish and swiss graduates of 
traditionalist seminaries for refusing to submit to papal 
authority the briton richard williamson 48 heads a 
traditionalist seminary in ridgefield conn 
an excommunicated catholic is not permitted to receive the 
churchs sacraments which include communion and extreme unction 
previously known as last rites 
no one is put to hell or condemned a vatican official said 
on condition of anonymity he lefebvre has put himself outside 
the communion of the church and takes responsibility before god 
during the fourhour ceremony the french archbishop told 
thousands who crowded the tent that he was creating new bishops as 
an operation of survival for his movement to ensure continuity 
of the church of all times 
lefebvre says the church has been infiltrated by wolves and 
thieves and is being consumed by the cancer of liberalism 
the lord may soon call me home he said thursday i must 
not leave you orphaned with no one to ordain new traditionalist 
priests 
john paul sent lefebvre a telegram wednesday urging him not to 
betray the episcopate and summoning him to rome at the 
consecration his audience laughed when the archbishop said the 
pope sent the official car of the papal nuncio to take him to rome 
the same night 
he called the vatican sanctions null and void and told his 
supporters not to pay any attention to them he said canon law 
permits his actions in a state of emergency which the vatican 
denies 
in a homily beginning the ceremony he renewed his argument that 
the vatican not he was on a schismatic course because it 
accepted errors once condemned that were leading to 
destruction of the church 
among those errors he said were ecumenism communism 
socialism and zionism 
this is not a schism we are not schismatic he said 
there is no question at all of this we are here to manifest our 
attachment to the church of all times 
we are convinced we are following the call of god we will 
wait until rome recognizes the value of our witness 
applause interrupted lefebvre several times a lone woman 
protester shouted we remain faithful to the pope in italian 
but no reaction was noticeable in the tent 
on wednesday the archbishop ordained 16 traditionalist priests 
bringing to nearly 250 the number he has ordained in defiance of 
the vatican since pope paul vi suspended him from priestly 
functions in 1976 
lefebvre himself was ordained in 1929 after obtaining degrees in 
philosophy and theology before his rebellion he was a missionary 
archbishop and papal representative in africa and a member of the 
commission that prepared the second vatican council whose reforms 
he rejected 
a vatican spokesman has said that lefebvres supporters numbered 
80000 to 100000 but other vatican officials have said about half 
a million people turn to his priests for various church functions 
thousands of people who could not get into the tent thursday 
listened to loudspeakers outside for those who did not understand 
french priests gave summaries of the homily in german and english 
of lebvres homily 
about 20 small confessionals were set up around the tent and 
many people used them organizers estimated the total audience at 
nearly 10000 
just before noon lefebvre ended the consecration ceremony by 
laying his hands on the four bishops as they knelt before him 
facing the altar they then received the symbols of office miter 
ring and crooked pastoral staff 
assisting him was antonio de castro mayer the only catholic 
bishop who has publicly supported lefebvre 
ordained as bishops and excommunicated thursday were williamson 
a convert from the anglican church bernard tissier de mallerais 
43 secretarygeneral of lefebvres fraternity alfonso de 
galarreta 31 spanishborn head of the seminary in la reja 
argentina and bernard fellay 30 a swiss who is chief 
administrator of the fraternity 
