the united states never has succeeded in deploying a mobile 
intercontinental ballistic missile in large part because of 
community opposition and had demanded that such weapons be banned 
under a proposed strategic arms reduction treaty now under 
negotiation with the kremlin 
but at last months moscow summit diplomats offered a proposal 
to allow a set number of mobile missiles within tightly defined 
geographical areas that could be inspected by satellites or teams 
from each country that proposal will be debated when negotiations 
resume in geneva next month 
the air force wants to deploy 25 mx trains each carrying two of 
the peacekeeper missiles 
they would be kept at fe warren air force base in cheyenne 
wyo in peacetime then scatter along the civilian rail system in 
times of eastwest tension or war making them difficult targets 
and a deterrence against a surprise soviet nuclear attack 
up to four more trains might be deployed later at as many as 10 
other air force bases 
so far congress has approved deployment of 50 mxs to be based 
