my how things have changed the chevrolet 
cavalier a humdrum compact first introduced in the 1982 model 
year as an import fighter has been transformed into a latterday 
muscle car in a newfor1988 model the cavalier z24 
listen to the rumble of the 28liter fuelinjected v6 feel 
the power as the goodyear eagle gt 4 tires grab the road hear 
them squeal as the car races ahead 
hunker into the comfortable somewhat sporty seats and get 
ready for a fine ride in a reasonably priced car 13209 out the 
door for the test car 
chevrolet first tried out the sporty z24 concept on the cavalier 
two years ago but its only in the 1988 model year that the 
general motors corp division has started to hit the mark 
the 1988 cavalier z24 coupe is a nice mix of sport styling 
including air dam on the front and rocker extensions and oldtime 
american car performance the v6 coupled with a fivespeed manual 
transmission in the test car was responsive 
however the transmission could feel a bit notchy it was easy 
to drive the car hard feel the responsiveness but those quick 
starts took a toll on fuel economy 
the suspension firm but still offering a nice ride was 
commendable 
exterior and interior fit and finish was excellent seats were 
comfortable though not fitted with all the gadgets such as 
adjustable lumbar support that are found in some other sporty cars 
the dashboard was easy to read with traditional gauges though 
an electronic instrument cluster is available a light came on to 
tell the driver when to shift slightly annoying until you get 
used to it 
interior leg room was fine in the front but could be miniscule 
in the rear if the front seats were moved all the way back 
the rear deck lid was a bit heavy but was designed so that 
anyone hoisting items into the trunk would not have to lift them 
over the car body just ease them over the bumper inside the 
trunk was flat and spacious 
chevrolet reports that sales of the z24 have been going well 
the division had a 50day supply in early may compared with a 
70day supply a year earlier and a second shift at one of the z24 
plants has been requested in anticipation of additional demand 
